---
// src/pages/fr/legal.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Header } from '@/components/Header';
import { Footer } from '@/components/Footer';

const title = "Informations Légales | WorkflowLeaf";
const description = "Conditions d'utilisation, politique de confidentialité, avertissements et coordonnées pour WorkflowLeaf.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} lang="fr" currentPath="/fr/legal">
  <Header client:load />
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 text-foreground bg-background min-h-screen">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">Informations Légales</h1>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-6 border-b border-border pb-2">Conditions d'utilisation</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Bienvenue chez WorkflowLeaf. En accédant ou en utilisant ce site web (workflowleaf.com) et nos services, vous acceptez d'être lié par ces Conditions d'utilisation ("Conditions"). Si vous êtes en désaccord avec une partie quelconque des conditions, vous ne pouvez pas accéder au site web ni utiliser nos services.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Les détails spécifiques de nos services de consultation et de mise en œuvre d'automatisation, y compris la portée, les livrables, les échéanciers et les modalités de paiement, sont définis dans des contrats ou propositions clients individuels distincts qui prévalent sur toute information générale fournie ici.
      </p>
       <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Utilisation du site web</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Toutes les informations fournies sur ce site web sont à titre informatif général uniquement et ne constituent pas un conseil professionnel ou juridique. Bien que nous nous efforcions de maintenir les informations à jour et exactes, nous ne faisons aucune déclaration ni garantie d'aucune sorte, expresse ou implicite, quant à l'exhaustivité, l'exactitude, la fiabilité, la pertinence ou la disponibilité concernant le site web ou les informations, produits, services ou graphiques associés contenus sur le site web à quelque fin que ce soit. Toute confiance que vous accordez à ces informations est donc strictement à vos propres risques.
      </p>
       <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Vous acceptez de ne pas utiliser le site web d'une manière qui cause, ou pourrait causer, des dommages au site web ou une altération de la disponibilité ou de l'accessibilité du site web ; ou de toute manière qui est illégale, illicite, frauduleuse ou nuisible.
      </p>
       <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Propriété Intellectuelle</h3>
       <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Le contenu de ce site web, y compris les textes, graphiques, logos et images, est la propriété de WorkflowLeaf (Simon Paris) et est protégé par le droit d'auteur et d'autres lois sur la propriété intellectuelle, sauf indication contraire.
      </p>
       <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Modification des Conditions</h3>
       <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        WorkflowLeaf se réserve le droit de modifier ces Conditions à tout moment. Nous informerons les utilisateurs des changements importants en mettant à jour la date au bas de this page. Your continued use of the site after such modifications constitutes your acceptance of the new Terms.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Governing Law</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        These Terms shall be governed and construed in accordance with the laws of the Province of Québec and the federal laws of Canada applicable therein, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-6 border-b border-border pb-2">Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        WorkflowLeaf ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal information in compliance with the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA) and Québec’s Law 25 (An Act to modernize legislative provisions as regards the protection of personal information).
      </p>
       <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Information We Collect</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        We collect personal information you voluntarily provide to us through contact forms, discovery calls, email communications, service agreements, and potentially through the use of cookies or similar technologies on our website (e.g., for analytics). This information may include your name, email address, phone number, company details, and any other information you choose to provide relevant to our services.
      </p>
       <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">How We Use Your Information</h3>
       <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Your personal information is used to:
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Communicate with you regarding inquiries and service delivery.</li>
          <li>Provide, operate, and maintain our automation consulting and implementation services.</li>
          <li>Process payments and manage client accounts (as defined in service agreements).</li>
          <li>Improve our website, services, and user experience (e.g., through anonymized analytics).</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
       <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Data Sharing and Disclosure</h3>
       <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        We do not sell your personal data to third parties. We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or servicing you (e.g., cloud hosting providers, CRM platforms, payment processors, email service providers), so long as those parties agree to keep this information confidential and secure. We may also disclose information when required by law. Some of these providers may operate outside of Québec or Canada; we take reasonable steps to ensure your data is protected according to applicable laws.
      </p>
       <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Your Rights & Consent</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        You have the right to access the personal information we hold about you, request corrections, or withdraw your consent to its use (subject to legal or contractual restrictions) at any time. To exercise these rights, please contact our Privacy Officer. Your use of our website and services signifies your consent to this Privacy Policy.
      </p>
       <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Data Security & Retention</h3>
       <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical security measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, or as required by law.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Cookies</h3>
       <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Our website may use cookies to enhance user experience and analyze site traffic. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings. [Optional: Link to a separate Cookie Policy if you have one].
      </p>
       <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Privacy Officer</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        The person responsible for the protection of personal information at WorkflowLeaf is Simon Paris. For any privacy inquiries or requests regarding your personal information, please contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@workflowleaf.com" class="text-primary-main underline hover:text-primary-hover">legal@workflowleaf.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-6 border-b border-border pb-2">Disclaimers & Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Disclaimer of Warranties:</strong> This website and our services are provided "as is" and "as available" without any warranties, express or implied, including but not limited to the implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement. We do not guarantee specific automation outcomes, cost savings, or return on investment, as results depend heavily on individual client systems, processes, data quality, and implementation context.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Limitation of Liability:</strong> To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, WorkflowLeaf and its founder, Simon Paris, shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits or revenues, whether incurred directly or indirectly, or any loss of data, use, goodwill, or other intangible losses, resulting from (a) your access to or use of or inability to access or use the website or services; (b) any conduct or content of any third party on the services; (c) any content obtained from the services; and (d) unauthorized access, use, or alteration of your transmissions or content. Our total liability for any claims arising out of or relating to these Terms or the services, where applicable by law, is limited to the amount you paid us, if any, for the specific services giving rise to the claim.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-6 border-b border-border pb-2">Contact Information</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        For any legal or privacy questions regarding these terms or our practices, please contact WorkflowLeaf via email: <a href="mailto:legal@workflowleaf.com" class="text-primary-main underline hover:text-primary-hover">legal@workflowleaf.com</a>.
      </p>
       <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-8">
        Dernière mise à jour : 22 avril 2025
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer client:load />
</Layout>
